The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                South 24-Parganas police met representatives of over 60 educational institutions in Alipore to review security measures on their premises. The cops suggested a string of measures, such as issuing photo IDs to students and staff, banning vehicles on campus, installing CCTV cameras and equipping guards with metal detectors.     High court Chief Justice S.S. Nijjar has assigned Justice D.P. Sengupta to hear the bail plea of Ashok Todi. Two days back, two judges of a high court division bench had held contradictory opinions on granting bail to the prime accused in the Rizwanur case and the matter was sent to the chief justice.    Subrata Das, 19, was killed in Thakurpukur on Wednesday while riding pillion on a friends motorcycle, which rammed into a CSTC bus. Das was taken to hospital, where he was declared dead. Dass friend fled. The bus driver later surrendered.                                                                                                                                                              
